- Use Radix primitives as building blocks for custom components
- Implement accessibility features using the built-in ARIA attributes
- Customize the look and feel using CSS or styled-components
- Utilize the provided hooks like `useSelect` for managing component state
- Follow the composition patterns recommended by Radix for complex components